    • Method Detail

      • $

        public static org.openqa.selenium.WebElement $(org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext $receiver,
                                               java.lang.String selector,
                                               int index)

        Find the nth element that can be located by the given CSS selector.

        This is an alternative to the find method.

        // Given the Kotlin's website index page with content elements
class IndexPage(browser: Browser) : Page(browser) {

    override val url = "https://kotlinlang.org/"

    override val at = at {
        title == "Kotlin Programming Language"
    }

    val navItems by lazy {
        `$`("a.nav-item", 0..2).map { it.text }
    }

    val tryItBtn by lazy {
        `$`(".try-button", 0).text
    }

    val features by lazy {
        `$`("li.kotlin-feature", 3, 2, 1, 0).`$`("h3:nth-child(2)", 0..3).map {
            it.text
        }
    }
}

Browser.drive(driverFactory) {
    // When I visit such page and get the content's elements
    to(::IndexPage).run {
        // Then I should get the navigation items
        assertEquals(navItems, listOf("Learn", "Community", "Try Online"))

        // And I should get the try-it button
        assertEquals(tryItBtn, "Try online")

        // And I should get the coolest features
        assertEquals(features, listOf("Concise", "Safe", "Interoperable", "Tool-friendly").reversed())
    }
}

        Parameters:
        selector - the CSS selector to be used for locating the element.
        index - the index of the element to be returned.
        Returns:
        The nth matching element.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - for an illegal index value.

        Find all the elements that can be located by the given CSS selector, restricted by the specified range.

        This is an alternative to the find method.

        Parameters:
        selector - the CSS selector to be used for locating the elements.
        range - specify the indices of the elements to be returned.
        Returns:
        The matching elements restricted by the specified range.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - for illegal index values within the range.

      • $

        public static java.util.List<org.openqa.selenium.WebElement> $(org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext $receiver,
                                                               java.lang.String selector,
                                                               int indices)

        Find all the elements that can be located by the given CSS selector, restricted by the specified indices. (If no index is provided, then all matching elements will be returned.)

        This is an alternative to the find method.

        // Given the Kotlin's website index page with content elements
class IndexPage(browser: Browser) : Page(browser) {

    override val url = "https://kotlinlang.org/"

    override val at = at {
        title == "Kotlin Programming Language"
    }

    val navItems by lazy {
        `$`("a.nav-item", 0..2).map { it.text }
    }

    val tryItBtn by lazy {
        `$`(".try-button", 0).text
    }

    val features by lazy {
        `$`("li.kotlin-feature", 3, 2, 1, 0).`$`("h3:nth-child(2)", 0..3).map {
            it.text
        }
    }
}

Browser.drive(driverFactory) {
    // When I visit such page and get the content's elements
    to(::IndexPage).run {
        // Then I should get the navigation items
        assertEquals(navItems, listOf("Learn", "Community", "Try Online"))

        // And I should get the try-it button
        assertEquals(tryItBtn, "Try online")

        // And I should get the coolest features
        assertEquals(features, listOf("Concise", "Safe", "Interoperable", "Tool-friendly").reversed())
    }
}

        Parameters:
        selector - the CSS selector to be used for locating the elements.
        indices - the indices of the elements to be returned.
        Returns:
        The matching elements restricted by the specified indices. (Or all matching elements if no index is provided.)
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - for illegal index values.
